The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Panaji, Aug. 21 (PTI): An Indian Navy fighter aircraft today crashed off the Goa coast, killing the pilot.          
	The Indian naval Sea Harrier aircraft, which was on a routine exercise mission, crashed about 11.57am, a navy spokesperson said. He also confirmed the death of Lieutenant Commander Saurav Saxena.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A special court hearing the Mumbai attack case has allowed prime accused Ajmal Kasab and two others to observe the Roza (fast) during Ramazan. The judge said he would instruct the jailer to facilitate the fast from Saturday.                  
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): Police on Thursday saved a call centre employee from being kidnapped by her former fiance and three of his aides. Akshi Bhatia was coming out of the call centre when the four dragged her into a car. Her colleagues gave chase and informed the police who intercepted the car. Three of the accused, including advocate Dilip Verma, were arrested.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): More than 130 Delhi police personnel face corruption cases, the police have said in response to an RTI application. Cases are pending against eight inspectors, 12 sub-inspectors, 18 assistant sub-inspectors, 28 head constables and 67 constables, the reply said.                   
	 Chikmagalur (PTI): Police were engaged in a gun battle with a 10- member gang of Naxalites near Karnatakas Chikmagalur district on Friday. The Maoists had opened fire when the police asked them to surrender. There were no reports of casualties.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Centre will grant unique human heritage status to the extinction-threatened Shompen tribe of the Andaman and Nicobar islands. The Centre is working on a draft policy that will restrict outside intervention in the life and culture of the tribe.                                                                                                                           
